editorialSummary.text: Restaurant serving housemade noodles and authentic Chinese recipes, plus specialty teas in an intimate setting.

originalText.text: Lovely atmosphere and waiter was accommodating to dietary restrictions and gluten free (rice noodles!) but the food was below average. The chicken noodle soup was bland and buttery. It lacked a flavor. Thr chicken was bone-in which is hard to eat with chopsticks. The spicy beef was not too spicy to bite, but the aftertaste left your mouth on fire! It had more flavor than the soup. But the food just isn’t worth coming back for.

originalText.text: We went there for dinner on a Sunday night, their closing time was 10pm on the website. We entered at 9:10pm , we were seated right away but never did we realize that their service will be so bad. They almost kicked us out of the restaurant as soon as it was 9:55 pm. Their service needs to change or change the closing time and don’t seat guests if you are in such a hurry to go home, nobody wants to stay in a restaurant. This is the first time actually we had this kind of experience after going to several restaurants across 3 different continents. The waiter was forcing us to pack our food and said “ you haven’t yet touched this , you should pack this” and literally started touching our food and ready to pack without our permission. We were finishing our dishes very fast and trying to leave but what they did as unacceptable. There was this Asian guy who told us he is the manager but he too was very inconsiderate, even after paying they didn’t allow us to atleast finish our food and leave and it was just 10 pm then, not that we have overstayed a lot . Change your closing time if you are in such a hurry to close. Also it was very uncomfortable as all 7-8 workers were staring at us since we were the last table for the night. The food was good actually , had their service been better and had they been more considerate, we could have provided good feedback but the management needs to address these service issues and change closing time keeping some buffer so that you don’t have to push and force guests to leave without finishing their food!!!

originalText.text:
We got the Crispy Spicy Wings, Dandan noodle, Sautéed Eggplant, the Sole Fish in clay pot, and soybean pudding for dessert.

I would happily order the dandan, sole, and soybean pudding again.

The wings were juicy with a nice 5 spice flavor, but nothing remarkable. The Dandan was fantastic and full of rich, umami flavor. The eggplant was soft and savory, but I found the sauce overpoweringly sweet. The fish was soft with a crisp exterior and I especially enjoyed how it came with big chunks of garlic. Finally, the soybean pudding was a refreshing and light complement to end the meal.

originalText.text: This restaurant is well decorated and the atmosphere is welcoming. Ordered Lamb Belly Noodle and Chickpea Noodle, and both turned out to be VERY, VERY, VERY oily. Quantity of the noodle was very small with four pieces of lamb belly in the bowl. Chickpea Noodle had a better looking but again the soup was mixed with huge amount of oil. Only try them if you don't mind drinking oil.

originalText.text:
Love this place, from entering with the atmosphere, being seated by great service to enjoying the delicious food!!

I really like how each dish is relatively of a small portion so that I can try different things!!!

The new eggplant dish is surprisingly spicy and delicious!!
Love their wonton and weekly soup too!!

Love the decorations! The service of the staff is great!! The food is yummy!! Highly recommend it!!
